  "text": "Stemness and differentiation were until recently largely treated as alternative outcomes of a binary decision made by a stem cell. This cell fate decision would globally govern the subsequent behaviour of these cells ( Figure 7A ), while the niche acted upstream to influence this decision [CITATION_1] . However, such a model cannot easily account for niches, e.g. in the mammalian intestine [CITATION_2] , that exhibit high plasticity and where cells adopt different functions according to need.",
